Yes, you will be moved into the first position of the waitlist in the class.

This is a position from where you are extremely likely to get back into in.

But sure, there's no guarantee.

children.subject:
That's not a possible numeric combination. Since all students who are waitlisted in the lab are also waitlisted in the class, your position on the waitlist for the lab must be smaller or equal to than your position on the waitlist for the class.

Let's say you're currently enrolled.

You try to switch into a full section, and get waitlisted.

You are now first on the waitlist for the class, which implies that you are first on the waitlist for the lecture and first on the waitlist for the lab.

Now, before any seats open up, four more people do the same thing. 2 try to switch into the same section you want, and 2 try to switch into other sections.

The result is that you are fifth on the waitlist for the class, and third on the waitlist for your section.
